The article discusses the importance of literacy and celebrates Read Across America Day. It emphasizes the value of reading in expanding knowledge, promoting curiosity, and fostering creativity. The article acknowledges that not all children have equal access to books and educational opportunities, particularly in underserved communities. The Biden administration is committed to improving literacy by investing in schools, supporting educators, and promoting adult literacy programs. The article calls for nurturing children's love for reading and making education meaningful and accessible. President Biden proclaims March 2, 2023, as Read Across America Day and encourages the participation of children, families, educators, and the public in observing the day.